Preheat the oven to 220C/425F/Gas 7.Place all the filling ingredients into a frying pan and gently saut√© for 2-3 minutes.Place into the oven and finish cooking for a further five minutes.Meanwhile, heat a griddle and when it's smoking add on the pittas and cook for 1-2 minutes on each side.To serve, stuff the pittas with the tomato and chickpea mixture.